        <p>The best thing about podcasts for a single dad is that they work while you're doing something else. These are worth putting in your rotation.</p>

        <h2>Dad-focused</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>
            <strong>The Dad Edge Podcast — Larry Hagner</strong><br>
            Long-running show focused on fatherhood and personal development for dads. Hagner is a single dad himself. Covers presence, co-parenting, identity, and building a life you're proud of. Practical without being self-helpy.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Single Dad Nation</strong><br>
            One of the few podcasts made specifically by and for single fathers. Interviews with other single dads plus practical topics that come up in single-parent life.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Good Dads Podcast</strong><br>
            Community-focused show on fatherhood. Covers a range of situations including divorce, custody, and single parenting alongside more general fatherhood topics.
          </li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Parenting</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>
            <strong>Big Life Journal Podcast</strong><br>
            Focused on raising kids with resilience and a growth mindset. Short episodes, practical and evidence-backed. Works well for any parenting situation.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Your Parenting Mojo — Jen Lumanlan</strong><br>
            Deep-dive research-based episodes on parenting topics. More academic than most but genuinely useful when you want to understand the "why" behind something your kid is doing.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Unruffled — Janet Lansbury</strong><br>
            Q&amp;A format focused on handling difficult behavior calmly. Straightforward and non-judgmental. Useful for parents of toddlers through middle-schoolers.
          </li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Divorce and co-parenting</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>
            <strong>The Co-Parenting Podcast</strong><br>
            Practical guidance on co-parenting communication, conflict reduction, and building systems that work for the kids. Covers both cooperative and high-conflict situations.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Divorced Girl Smiling Podcast — Jackie Pilossoph</strong><br>
            Despite the name, the content covers divorce from multiple angles and includes topics relevant to both men and women — attorneys, financial planning, dating again, and emotional recovery.
          </li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Mental health and personal development</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>
            <strong>The Art of Manliness Podcast — Brett McKay</strong><br>
            Broad-ranging show on topics relevant to men — mental health, relationships, physical health, finances, career. Not single-dad specific but consistently high quality and relevant.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Therapy for Black Men — DeRay Davis</strong><br>
            Focused on mental health for Black men, but widely listened to across audiences. Covers therapy, relationships, fatherhood, and breaking the pattern of not asking for help.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Feel Better, Live More — Dr. Rangan Chatterjee</strong><br>
            Long-form conversations on mental and physical health. Good on stress, sleep, and sustainable lifestyle habits — all relevant when you're running on fumes as a single parent.
          </li>
        </ul>

        <div class="callout">
          <p><strong>Where to listen:</strong> All of these are available free on Spotify, Apple Podcasts, and most podcast apps. Search the title and hit subscribe — no account required on most platforms.</p>
        </div>
